The paper deals with privacy-preserving search over genomic data, which is a sensitive and personal type of data. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the category of "Cryptology and Security" (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of cloud storage and indexing techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of "Databases" (cs.DB) and "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper deals with access control policies and fine-grained encryption, which could place it in the categories of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CY) and "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR).
